  "descriptions": {
    "en": {
      "language": "en",
      "value": "feudal lord from the early to mid-Edo period of Japan. He was the eldest son of Taneharu Akizuki, the second lord of the Hyuga Takanabe domain, and the third lord of the Takanabe domain (the 19th head of the Akizuki clan). Junior Fifth Rank, Lower"
    },
    "ja": {
      "language": "ja",
      "value": "日本の江戸時代前期～中期の大名。日向高鍋藩2代藩主秋月種春長男で、高鍋藩3代藩主（秋月氏19代当主）。従五位下佐渡守。御家騒動「上方下方騒動」の中心人物で、解決に導いた"
    }
  },
